00:29:00.230 --> 00:29:02.810
so we don't have to fight to often.

00:29:02.810 --> 00:29:04.590
&gt;&gt; You don't do four hand?

00:29:04.590 --> 00:29:06.580
&gt;&gt; Again, the courting ritual
was a lot of four hands

00:29:06.580 --> 00:29:08.130
which it turns out was a big thing.

00:29:08.130 --> 00:29:09.430
Did you read that article?

00:29:09.430 --> 00:29:12.000
There was something in The Times
I think that talked about sort

00:29:12.000 --> 00:29:15.950
of the origin of four hand piano
was that it was back in the 1800s,

00:29:15.950 --> 00:29:19.570
it was a way to sit in a salon, a
man and a woman would sit together

00:29:19.570 --> 00:29:22.690
and play four hands and that the
really craft four hand arrangements

00:29:22.690 --> 00:29:25.630
involved a lot of reaching hands
over each other and doing things

00:29:25.630 --> 00:29:31.040
like that, and that part of it
was to allow husbands and wives

00:29:31.040 --> 00:29:33.790
but also not husbands
and wives to interact

00:29:33.790 --> 00:29:36.800
with each other very closely in
that way, so we did a lot of that.

00:29:36.800 --> 00:29:40.590 position:56%
We don't do an awful lot of four
hands now but again, whenever we get

00:29:40.590 --> 00:29:44.440
to the piano now it's
usually for work so it's not

00:29:44.440 --> 00:29:46.690
as much of that as I would like.

00:29:46.690 --> 00:29:49.110
&gt;&gt; Well we got through
