00:29:49.110 --> 00:29:52.610
&gt;&gt; All right good.

00:29:52.610 --> 00:29:55.340
&gt;&gt; In a master class you gave,
you talked about the importance

00:29:55.340 --> 00:29:58.550
of staging what you write
as you're writing it.

00:29:58.550 --> 00:30:02.940
At what point in the process

00:30:02.940 --> 00:30:07.670
as you're writing are you picturing
what the performers might be doing

00:30:07.670 --> 00:30:08.970
on the stage?

00:30:08.970 --> 00:30:10.270
Does that come afterwards?

00:30:10.270 --> 00:30:12.600
&gt;&gt; Yeah, I don't know if it's as
specific as sort of saying you have

00:30:12.600 --> 00:30:16.030
to walk four steps left here you
know, that I'm going to leave

00:30:16.030 --> 00:30:18.520
to someone else to
stage it but it is

00:30:18.520 --> 00:30:23.510 position:56%
about knowing what the actors are
doing you know, what are they trying

00:30:23.510 --> 00:30:26.760
to do and so I think I
would say to an actor know

00:30:26.760 --> 00:30:28.700
in your head what your
staging is going to be

00:30:28.700 --> 00:30:31.300
so that you know how
the song sort of works

00:30:31.300 --> 00:30:34.290
because this first A section
is going to be one thing

00:30:34.290 --> 00:30:35.980
and the second A section
is going to be another

00:30:35.980 --> 00:30:39.020
so is there something
physical you can do to explain

00:30:39.020 --> 00:30:42.560
to yourself why you're changing
track, what all that is.

00:30:42.560 --> 00:30:46.760
There are times where I will
write a song where it is not clear

00:30:46.760 --> 00:30:50.470
to me how the song is
supposed to work on stage.

00:30:50.470 --> 00:30:52.700
I'll have just gone off
someplace and really been excited

00:30:52.700 --> 00:30:55.940
about a certain idea musically or
a certain idea lyrically and so

00:30:55.940 --> 00:31:00.110
for me, at that point I usually am
going to sit and say what do I want

00:31:00.110 --> 00:31:03.900
to say to the director about
how this could be staged

00:31:03.900 --> 00:31:05.200
so that they don't say to me well,

00:31:05.200 --> 00:31:06.770
this doesn't make any
sense, let's just cut it.

00:31:06.770 --> 00:31:09.710
Because if I can defend
it then I can keep it.

00:31:09.710 --> 00:31:12.240
If I really love it then
what I want to be able to say

00:31:12.240 --> 00:31:15.240
to the director is you don't
have to use this but it could be

00:31:15.240 --> 00:31:18.520
that this section takes place,
here it is there's a section

00:31:18.520 --> 00:31:22.470
of Shiksa Goddess even when it was
the song before Shiksa Goddess,

00:31:22.470 --> 00:31:24.520
I Could be in Love With Someone
Like You but that section

00:31:24.520 --> 00:31:27.070
of the song the state direction
always is maybe they're walking

00:31:27.070 --> 00:31:29.710
in the park and that's
printed I think in the libretto

00:31:29.710 --> 00:31:33.440 position:56%
because it doesn't matter to me what
they're doing but if that's the way

00:31:33.440 --> 00:31:35.740
that gets you to this
chunk of the song great,

00:31:35.740 --> 00:31:37.040
maybe they're walking
through the park here.

00:31:37.040 --> 00:31:38.940
Maybe that's the thing that
they're doing but what you need

00:31:38.940 --> 00:31:41.650
to know is this isn't the same
place as where they just were.

00:31:41.650 --> 00:31:43.710
Something different is
happening now and so you

00:31:43.710 --> 00:31:45.490
as the director are
obliged to deal with that,

00:31:45.490 --> 00:31:47.410
you as the actor are
obliged to deal with that

00:31:47.410 --> 00:31:49.150
or the song is going
to feel sort of static.

00:31:49.150 --> 00:31:50.450
You're going to feel stuck there.

00:31:50.450 --> 00:31:54.990 position:56%
&gt;&gt; Do you remember when you wrote
The Schmuel Song, how you visualized

00:31:54.990 --> 00:31:56.680
in your head how it
would be performed?

00:31:56.680 --> 00:31:59.230
&gt;&gt; Well Schmuel no, I think
Schmuel because it was

00:31:59.230 --> 00:32:01.570
so clearly performative
because Schmuel is clearly

00:32:01.570 --> 00:32:05.370
about a guy showing off this
thing, I figured they'd figure it

00:32:05.370 --> 00:32:07.900
out one way or the other
so that was really,

00:32:07.900 --> 00:32:10.640
I thought that was just going
to be a buffet, which it was,

00:32:10.640 --> 00:32:14.430
just something for Daisy and
